After Jesus had dismissed the crowds, He went aboard the boat and came to the region of Magadan.
Jesus is asked for a wondrous sign.
The Pharisees and Sadducees came to test Jesus. They asked him to show them a sign from heaven.
He replied, "In the evening, you see the sky. You say, 'The weather will be good. The sky is red.'"
In the morning you say, "Today there will be a storm. The sky is red and cloudy." You know the meaning of what you see in the sky. But you cannot understand the signs of what is happening now.
"An evil and adulterous generation seeks after a sign! And no sign will be given to it except the sign of Jonah." And He left them and went away. The leaven of the Pharisees and Sadducees
Pupils crossed to the other side of the lake, forgetting to bring bread.
"Beware," Jesus said to them, "Beware of the leaven of the Pharisees and Sadducees."
The students talked about this among themselves and said, "He must mean this because we didn't bring any bread."
Jesus knew what they were saying, and he said to them, "You of little faith! Why are you talking among yourselves about having no bread?"
Don't you understand yet? Don't you remember the five loaves for the five thousand? Don't you remember how many baskets full we gathered?
Don't you remember the seven loaves for the four thousand? Don't you remember how many baskets were collected?
How is it that you don't understand? I didn't talk to you about bread. But beware of the yeast of the Pharisees and Sadducees.
Then the disciples understood that Jesus was not speaking of the wine used in the bread, but was warning them against the teachings of the Pharisees and Sadducees. Peter says that Jesus is the Christ.
Jesus went on to the region of Caesarea Philippi. There he asked his disciples, "Who do people say the Son of Man is?"
They replied, "Some say John the Baptist; others say Elijah; still others say Jeremiah or one of the prophets."
"But what does it matter to you?" he asked. "Who do you think I am?"
Simon Peter answered, "You are the Christ, the Son of the living God."
Jesus answered, "Blessed are you, Simon son of Jonah! For flesh and blood has not revealed this to you, but my Father who is in heaven."
This is what I tell you. You are Peter. On this rock, I will build my church. The gates of hell shall not prevail against it.
I will give you the keys of the kingdom of heaven. Whatever you bind on earth will be bound in heaven, and whatever you loose on earth will be loosed in heaven.
Then Jesus warned his disciples not to tell anyone that he was the Christ. Jesus speaks about his upcoming death.
From that time on, Jesus began to explain to his disciples that he must go to Jerusalem. There he will suffer many things from the elders, chief priests, and teachers of the law. He will be killed, and on the third day he will be raised from the dead.
Peter took Jesus aside and began to rebuke him, saying, "Far be it from you, Lord! This shall never happen to you!"
Jesus turned and said to Peter, "Get behind me, Satan! You are a stumbling block to me; for you are not setting your mind on the things of God, but on the things of man."
Then Jesus told his disciples, "If anyone wants to follow me, they must deny themselves, take up their cross, and follow me.
If he seems to love to destroy himself, he will lose himself. But if he loses himself for me, he will find himself.
"What good is it to gain the whole world and lose one's soul? Or what would one give in exchange for their soul?"
The Son of Man will come in his Father's glory, with his angels, and then he will reward each according to his works.
"What I am about to tell you is true. Some who are standing here will not taste death before they see the Son of Man coming in his kingdom."
"The transformation of Jesus"
Six days later, Jesus took with him Peter and James and John, the brother of James. He brought them up to a high mountain by themselves.
There, before them, his appearance changed. His face shone like the sun. His clothes became as white as light.
At that moment, Moses and Elijah appeared before them. Moses and Elijah were speaking with Jesus.
Peter said to Jesus, "Lord, it is good that we are here. If you wish, I will make three booths: one for you, one for Moses, and one for Elijah."
While Peter was still speaking, a bright cloud enveloped them, and a voice from the cloud said, "This is my beloved Son, with whom I am well pleased. Listen to him!"
When the disciples heard this, they were terrified. They fell to the ground with their faces down.
But Jesus came and touched them. "Get up," he said. "Don't be afraid."
When they raised their heads, they saw no one but Jesus.
They came down from the mountain. And as they were coming down, Jesus commanded them, "Tell no one what you have seen." He said to them, "Wait until the Son of Man has risen from the dead."
The disciples asked him, "Why do the scribes say that Elijah must come first?"
Jesus answered, "Yes. Elijah is to come and restore all things.
But I tell you, when the Son of Man comes, they will not recognize him. They will do to him whatever they want to do. That is how they will treat the Son of Man.
Then the disciples understood that Jesus was speaking to them about John the Baptist. Jesus healed a boy who had a demon.
As they approached the crowd, a man came up to Jesus. He knelt before him.
"Sir," he said, "have mercy on my son. He trembles violently and suffers greatly. He often falls into the fire or into the water.
I brought him to your children, but they couldn't find a cure for him.
"Oh people, you are a generation that does not believe, and your hearts are hardened!" Jesus replied. "How much longer shall I remain with you? How much longer shall I bear with you? Bring the child to me here."
Jesus commanded the demon to come out of the boy, and it did. The boy was healed at that very moment.
Then the disciples came to Jesus in private and asked, "Why couldn't we cast it out?"
He replied, "Because your faith is so small. What I am about to tell you is true. If you have faith as small as a mustard seed, it is enough. You can say to this mountain, 'Move from here to there,' and it will move. Nothing will be impossible for you."
