Jesus and his disciples arrived at Capernaum. There, the tax collectors came to Peter and asked him, "Does your teacher not pay the temple tax?"
"Ah, he does it this way," you replied. When Peter entered the house, Jesus was the first to speak. "What do you think, Simon?" he asked. "Who do the kings of the earth collect taxes and duties from? Do they collect them from their own children or from others?"
"From others," Peter answered. "Then the sons do not have to pay," Jesus told him.
"But I don't want to annoy them. Why don't you go to the lake and cast your net? Take the first fish you catch. Open its mouth. Inside, you'll find the coin you need exactly. Take it and give it to them on my behalf and yours."
